The Reducto MCP server is an open-standard integration that enables AI agents in tools like Claude Desktop, Cursor, and VS Code to process documents directly [1][2]. It allows agents to classify, parse, extract data from, split, and edit documents without requiring custom glue code [1][3].

You can choose between two deployment options:

The hosted server (`https://mcp.reducto.ai/mcp`) is the fastest to set up but cannot access local files; it requires documents to be provided via public URLs [1][3]. Add this to your MCP configuration:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "reducto": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "https://mcp.reducto.ai/mcp",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer your-api-key"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The local server is required for accessing files directly from your machine [1][3]. It is installed via `uvx` and automatically authenticates using your local Reducto CLI credentials [4][3]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "reducto": {
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": ["mcp-server-reducto"]
    }
  }
}
```

The server supports `jobid://` chaining, allowing agents to perform multi-step workflows—such as parsing a document once and then extracting data or splitting the document without re-processing [1][4]. Documents can be referenced via `https://` (public), `reducto://` (uploaded storage), or `jobid://` (previous processing results) [1][5].
